Florida college football fans should block off mid-April for a busy three days of spring games. The Gators will hold their annual exhibition at Ben Hill Griffin Stadium on Thursday April 13, UF announced Monday. It’s the second year in a row that the Gators will play on a Thursday night. More details about the event will be announced in the coming weeks. That Friday will be even busier. Miami announced Monday that its spring game will be on April 14 at Fort Lauderdale’s DRV PNK Stadium. UCF has previously announced that its exhibition will be that date, too, and a tentative spring football schedule for USF also has its game on the same day. Florida State’s game will be at 4 p.m. on April 15, the ACC Network announced Monday. It will be shown on ACCNX, the network’s digital platform. • • • Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.